Building on Windows (raw notes)
1. Using stack 1.4.0
2. Run from: C:\Users\{User}\AppData\Local\Programs\stack\x86_64-windows\msys2-20150512
    msys2_shell.cmd -mingw64
3. Following https://blogs.gnome.org/nacho/2014/08/01/how-to-build-your-gtk-application-on-windows/
    3.1. pacman -Syu
    3.2. pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-toolchain
    3.3. pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gtk2
    3.4. pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-zlib
4. In project's root run: 
    stack build
5. Prepare distribution tree, like this on Wiki binary distributables with exception to copy:
    threadscope.png and threadscope.ui to bin\ folder.